      "errorMessage": "task_id: ses_361dd69afffeiAAPHhP9ppzGQo (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nNow I have a comprehensive understanding of the entire codebase. Here is the detailed summary:\n\n---\n\n# Super-Ralph Agent Framework: Comprehensive Codebase Summary\n\n## 1. Project Overview\n\n**Super-Ralph** is a CLI-driven orchestration framework for AI-assisted software development. It bridges three external systems:\n- **OpenCode** (`@opencode-ai/sdk`) — an AI coding agent runtime\n- **Beads** (`br` CLI) — a dependency-aware task tracker\n- **Superpowers** — a structured intake methodology\n\nThe core concept is the **Ralph Loop**: a repeating SELECT → PROMPT → EXECUTE → EVALUATE cycle. Every phase (reverse, decompose, forward) runs through this same loop engine with phase-specific behavior injected via callbacks. The key design principle is **fresh context per iteration**: each agent session is isolated with no memory of prior iterations — the orchestrator carries all state.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Project Directory Structure\n\n```\nagent-framework/\n  src/                  # 19 TypeScript source modules\n  templates/            # Default .hbs Handlebars templates + config + agents.md\n  skills/               # Built-in question banks: feature.md, bug.md, hotfix.md, refactor.md\n  tests/\n    unit/               # Bun unit tests (run-state, reverse mock answers)\n    e2e-*.sh            # Bash E2E test scripts (dry-run + live)\n    fixtures/           # Fixture projects for testing\n  docs/\n    plans/              # Historical and current design documents\n    reference/          # Run artifacts reference docs\n  spec/\n    README.md           # Navigation guide\n    CONVENTIONS.md      # Clean-room spec writing rules\n    architecture/       # Architecture overview + runtime lifecycle docs\n    module-catalog.md   # Inventory of all 19 modules\n  .opencode/plugins/    # task_complete OpenCode plugin\n  .super-ralph/         # Runtime config and state (created by init)\n  .beads/               # Managed by br CLI\n  package.json, tsconfig.json, bun.lock\n  install.sh, uninstall.sh\n  README.md, AGENTS.md\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Main Modules and Their Responsibilities\n\n### Domain 1: CLI Entry Point\n\n**`src/index.ts`** — Process boundary. Parses CLI arguments (manual parser, not a library), dispatches to phase command functions or utility commands. Sets process exit code based on `LoopResult.failed`. No business logic.\n\nCommands dispatched: `forward` (alias: `run`), `decompose`, `reverse`, `init`, `status`, `doctor`, `help`.\n\n### Domain 2: Phases (the three top-level workflows)\n\n**`src/forward.ts`** — Implements the `forward` phase (beads → code). Constructs `PhaseCallbacks` that: query ready beads via `br ready`, pick the highest-priority one, render `forward.hbs`, and route to the appropriate model by bead area label. Signals stop when no ready beads remain or agent signals `phase_done`.\n\n**`src/decompose.ts`** — Implements the `decompose` phase (spec → beads). Creates an epic bead via `br create --type epic`, then iteratively prompts the agent to read the spec + list of created beads and produce the next bead. Loop continues until agent signals `phase_done` (all spec requirements covered). Max 50 iterations.\n\n**`src/reverse.ts`** — Implements the `reverse` phase (anything → spec). Has two code paths:\n- **Autonomous** (with inputs, no `--interactive`): uses `runPhaseLoop` normally; agent iteratively creates/refines a Markdown spec file. Max 20 iterations.\n- **Interactive** (no inputs, or with `--interactive`): spawns a separate event loop that intercepts `question.asked` SSE events and renders them via `@clack/prompts`. Does not use `runPhaseLoop`.\n- **Mixed** (inputs + `--interactive`): same as interactive, but inputs are passed as context.\n\n### Domain 3: Engine\n\n**`src/engine.ts`** — The shared loop engine. `runPhaseLoop(projectDir, callbacks, flags, onEvent?)` is the only export. Manages the full lifecycle: load config → setup → start/attach server → iterate (select → prompt → execute → evaluate) → shutdown. Applies error strategy (retry/skip/abort), emits typed events, writes run artifacts after each iteration.\n\n### Domain 4: Integrations\n\n**`src/opencode.ts`** — OpenCode server adapter. Functions: `startServer()` (spawns ephemeral server on random port, auto-fixes broken symlinks), `connectToServer(url)` (attach mode), `createSession(client, title)`, `runPrompt(...)` (sends prompt via `promptAsync`, streams SSE events to stdout via `StreamCapture`, extracts `task_complete` signal from session messages). Also `checkBrokenSymlinks()`, `showToast()`, `abortSession()`.\n\n**`src/interactive.ts`** — Interactive session handler. `runInteractiveSession(...)` subscribes to SSE events, intercepts `question.asked`, renders questions via `@clack/prompts` (single-select, multi-select, or custom text input). Supports mock answers from JSON file (`loadMockAnswers(path)`) for automated testing. Returns `InteractiveResult` with completion status, cost, tokens, and files changed.\n\n**`src/beads.ts`** — `br` CLI adapter. Functions: `runBr(args)` (spawns child process, parses JSON output), `getAllReady(epicId)`, `getBeadDetails(beadId)`, `closeBead(beadId)`, `getAllBeads(epicId)`, `getEpicProgress(epicId)`. Never reads `.beads/` directly; always shells out to `br`.\n\n### Domain 5: Infrastructure\n\n| Module | Role |\n|--------|------|\n| `src/config.ts` | Loads `.super-ralph/config.toml` via `@iarna/toml`, deep-merges with defaults, provides `resolveModel(labels, title, config, override)` |\n| `src/template.ts` | Loads and compiles Handlebars `.hbs` templates from `.super-ralph/`; `renderPrompt(template, vars)` |\n| `src/skills.ts` | Resolves skill names (`feature`, `bug`, `hotfix`, `refactor`) or arbitrary file paths to Markdown content |\n| `src/events.ts` | `EngineEvent` discriminated union, `EngineEventEmitter` pub/sub, `attachDefaultConsoleRenderer` (writes all events to stdout) |\n| `src/run-state.ts` | `startRunTracker(...)` creates `.super-ralph/runs/<runId>/`, writes `session.json` (live + global mirror), `events.jsonl`, and per-iteration transcripts |\n| `src/run-status.ts` | `getRunStatus(projectDir, runRef)` — reads artifacts back; resolves `\"latest\"` reference |\n| `src/progress.ts` | `appendProgress(...)` writes Markdown entries to `.super-ralph/progress.md`; `readRecentProgress(...)` reads the last N entries for agent context |\n| `src/output-parser.ts` | `StreamCapture` — accumulates raw SSE lines and display text (capped at 250,000 chars each) |\n| `src/timeout.ts` | `withTimeout(task, timeoutMs, errorMessage)` — `Promise.race` utility |\n| `src/init.ts` | `runInit(projectDir)` — one-time scaffolding: creates `.super-ralph/`, copies templates, writes config with auto-detected `cli.path`, installs `.opencode/plugins/super-ralph.js` + `bun install`, creates `tasks/`, runs `br init`, updates `AGENTS.md` |\n| `src/types.ts` | Central type definitions: `BeadInfo`, `LoopConfig`, `IterationResult`, `CompletionResult`, `LoopResult`, `PhaseFlags`, `ForwardFlags`, `DecomposeFlags`, `ReverseFlags`, `ErrorStrategy` |\n\n---\n\n## 4. User-Visible Workflows\n\n### `super-ralph init`\nSets up a project for first use. Creates all needed directories and files, installs the OpenCode plugin. Idempotent (skips existing files). Does not start a server.\n\n### `super-ralph reverse [inputs...] [options]`\nThree modes:\n1. **Interactive** (no inputs): Agent asks one question at a time via terminal prompts, then synthesizes a spec.\n2. **Autonomous** (with inputs): Agent analyzes files/URLs/descriptions and iteratively creates/refines a Markdown spec.\n3. **Mixed** (inputs + `--interactive`): Inputs as context, then interactive interview.\n\nOutput: spec file(s) in `docs/specs/` (or `--output` dir) and a copy in `tasks/`.\n\nKey options: `--skill <feature|bug|hotfix|refactor|path>`, `--output <dir>`, `--interactive`, `--answers <json>` (mock answers for testing), `--model`, `--max-iterations`, `--dry-run`, `--attach`.\n\n### `super-ralph decompose --spec <path> [options]`\nReads a spec/PRD file. Creates an epic bead. Iteratively prompts an agent to analyze the spec and create the next bead until all requirements are covered. Optionally adds review, bugscan, audit, and learning beads (controlled by config).\n\nKey options: `--epic-title <title>`, `--model`, `--max-iterations` (default 50), `--dry-run`.\n\n### `super-ralph forward --epic <ID> [options]`\nImplements beads in dependency order. Each iteration: picks the highest-priority ready bead, routes to the correct model by area label, prompts agent to implement → test → commit → close bead. Loop exits when no ready beads remain.\n\nKey options: `--model`, `--max-iterations` (default: 2× bead count), `--dry-run`, `--attach`.\n\n### `super-ralph status`\nTwo sub-modes:\n- `--epic <ID>`: Shows bead progress (completed/total, lists open and in-progress beads).\n- `--run <runId|latest>`: Shows run artifact state (status, iteration counters, last event, transcript path).\n\n### `super-ralph doctor [--fix]`\nValidates: bun, br CLI, `.super-ralph/` init, all three `.hbs` templates, `config.toml`, `.beads/` workspace, `cli.path`, and broken symlinks in `~/.config/opencode/`. With `--fix`, auto-removes broken symlinks.\n\n### `super-ralph help`\nPrints full usage text to stdout.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Key Interfaces, Entry Points, and Public APIs\n\n### Primary Entry Point\n`src/index.ts` — invoked as `bun run src/index.ts \"$@\"` by the shell wrapper installed in a writable bin directory.\n\n### Secondary Entry Point\n`.opencode/plugins/super-ralph.js` — loaded by the OpenCode server at startup. Registers the `task_complete` tool that agents call to signal completion. Not operator-invoked.\n\n### Core TypeScript API\n\n```typescript\n// Phase runner functions (called by CLI)\nrunForward(projectDir: string, flags: ForwardFlags): Promise<LoopResult>\nrunDecompose(projectDir: string, flags: DecomposeFlags): Promise<LoopResult>\nrunReverse(projectDir: string, flags: ReverseFlags): Promise<LoopResult>\nrunInit(projectDir: string): Promise<void>\n\n// Engine (called by phases)\nrunPhaseLoop(\n  projectDir: string,\n  callbacks: PhaseCallbacks,\n  flags: PhaseFlags,\n  onEvent?: EngineEventListener,\n): Promise<LoopResult>\n\n// PhaseCallbacks interface (phases implement this)\ninterface PhaseCallbacks {\n  setup(config: LoopConfig, dryRun: boolean): Promise<{ maxIterations: number; description: string }>;\n  nextIteration(config: LoopConfig, iteration: number): Promise<PhaseIteration | null>;\n  handleResult(result: CompletionResult, iteration: number): Promise<boolean>;\n}\n\n// OpenCode adapter\nstartServer(): Promise<ServerHandle>\nconnectToServer(url: string): Promise<ServerHandle>\ncreateSession(client, title): Promise<string>\nrunPrompt(client, sessionId, prompt, model, systemPrompt?, serverUrl?, inactivityTimeoutMs?): Promise<PromptResult>\n\n// Config\nloadConfig(projectDir: string): LoopConfig\nresolveModel(beadLabels, beadTitle, config, cliOverride?): { providerID, modelID }\n\n// Beads\nrunBr(args: string[], cwd?): Promise<unknown>\ngetAllReady(epicId): Promise<BeadInfo[]>\ngetAllBeads(epicId): Promise<BeadInfo[]>\ngetBeadDetails(beadId): Promise<BeadInfo>\ngetEpicProgress(epicId): Promise<{ total, completed, remaining }>\n\n// Run artifacts\nstartRunTracker(projectDir, description, maxIterations): RunTracker\ngetRunStatus(projectDir, runRef): RunStatus\n\n// Interactive (reverse phase)\nrunInteractiveSession(client, sessionId, prompt, model, systemPrompt?, inactivityTimeoutMs?): Promise<InteractiveResult>\nloadMockAnswers(filePath): void   // for test automation\nclearMockAnswers(): void\n```\n\n### task_complete Tool (Agent-facing API)\nAgents signal completion by calling this OpenCode tool:\n```\ntask_complete({ status: \"complete\" | \"phase_done\" | \"blocked\" | \"failed\", reason?: string })\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. Configuration Options\n\nConfiguration lives in `.super-ralph/config.toml`. Loaded once per run by `loadConfig()`, deep-merged with hardcoded defaults.\n\n```toml\n[engine]\ntimeout_minutes = 30            # Hard wall-clock limit per iteration\ninactivity_timeout_seconds = 180  # Max seconds with no SSE events before abort\niteration_delay_ms = 2000       # Sleep between iterations\nstrategy = \"retry\"              # \"retry\" | \"skip\" | \"abort\"\nmax_retries = 3                 # Retries per item when strategy=retry\n\n[opencode]\nurl = \"http://localhost:4096\"   # Unused (server is self-spawned); kept for --attach reference\n\n[cli]\npath = \"\"                       # Absolute path to src/index.ts (auto-set by init)\n\n[models]\ndefault = \"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6\"\n\n[models.areas]\n# Map area: labels to specific models\nfrontend-design = \"google/gemini-2.5-pro\"\nbackend = \"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6\"\nreview = \"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6\"\n\n[reverse]\noutput_dir = \"docs/specs\"       # Default output directory for spec files\n\n[decompose]\ninclude_review = true           # Add review beads\ninclude_bugscan = true          # Add bugscan beads\ninclude_audit = true            # Add audit bead\n```\n\n**Model resolution order:**\n1. CLI `--model` override (all iterations)\n2. Bead `area:X` label → `[models.areas].X`\n3. `[models].default`\n\n---\n\n## 7. Event Flows and Message Passing\n\n### Engine Event Flow (pub/sub)\n\nThe engine emits strongly-typed `EngineEvent` objects via `EngineEventEmitter`. Three subscribers are attached at the start of each run:\n1. **Console renderer** (`attachDefaultConsoleRenderer`) — writes human-readable text to stdout\n2. **Run tracker** (`startRunTracker`) — writes `events.jsonl` and updates `session.json`\n3. **External listener** (optional `onEvent` parameter) — for testing or TUI integration\n\nEvent types in emission order for a successful iteration:\n```\nloop.description\nserver.started | server.attached\nserver.attach_hint\niteration.started\niteration.session_created\niteration.completed | iteration.blocked | iteration.retrying | iteration.failed | iteration.error\nloop.completed\n```\n\n### Agent → Orchestrator Signaling\n\nThe only channel an agent uses to communicate outcome is the `task_complete` tool call registered via the OpenCode plugin. After the SSE stream goes idle (`session.idle` event), the engine reads `session.messages()` and scans for a `task_complete` tool call with `state.status === \"completed\"`. The `input.status` field determines the `CompletionResult`.\n\nIf no `task_complete` is found, the result is `status: \"stalled\"` which triggers the failure strategy.\n\n### Prompt Streaming (SSE)\n\n`runPrompt` and `runInteractiveSession` use `promptAsync` (non-blocking) + SSE event subscription:\n- `message.part.delta` → writes text deltas to stdout in real-time; captured by `StreamCapture`\n- `message.part.updated` (tool parts) → writes tool-call status lines (running/done/error)\n- `question.asked` (interactive only) → triggers `@clack/prompts` UI; answer sent via `question.reply`\n- `session.idle` → loop exits normally\n- `session.error` → loop exits with error text\n\nAn inactivity watchdog polls every 10 seconds; if no event arrives for `inactivity_timeout_seconds`, the session is aborted. A heartbeat prints to stdout every 30 seconds during active sessions.\n\n### Inter-Phase Communication\n\nPhases communicate exclusively through the filesystem and the `br` CLI. No in-process coupling:\n```\nreverse   → writes Markdown spec   → docs/specs/<name>.md\ndecompose → reads spec, br create  → .beads/ (via br CLI)\nforward   → br ready, implements   → project source files + git commits\n```\n\n---\n\n## 8. Error Handling and Failure Modes\n\n### Iteration-level failures\n\nWhen an agent returns `status: \"failed\"`, `\"stalled\"`, `\"timeout\"`, or `\"error\"`:\n\n| Strategy (`engine.strategy`) | Behavior |\n|-------------------------------|----------|\n| `retry` (default) | Decrement iteration counter; retry the same item up to `max_retries` times per label |\n| `abort` | Increment `failed`, emit `iteration.failed` with `action: \"aborting\"`, break the loop |\n| `skip` | Increment `failed`, emit `iteration.failed` with `action: \"skipping\"`, continue to next |\n\n### Exception-level failures\n\nUncaught exceptions inside the per-iteration `try` block: recorded as `status: \"error\"`, emit `iteration.error`, apply `abort` strategy if configured. The `finally` block always runs: finalize run tracker (status: `\"failed\"` if not already finalized), close the server.\n\n### Timeout failures\n\nTwo guards:\n- **Hard timeout**: `withTimeout` wraps each `runPrompt` call; rejects after `timeout_minutes * 60 * 1000` ms.\n- **Inactivity timeout**: Inside SSE event loop, watchdog fires every 10s; if idle for `inactivity_timeout_seconds`, throws. On either timeout, best-effort `session.abort()` is called.\n\n### Blocking\n\n`status: \"blocked\"` increments `skipped` (not `failed`), emits `iteration.blocked`. Does not trigger retry strategy. `handleResult` can still return `true` to continue the loop with the next item.\n\n### Phase_done handling\n\n`phase_done` is treated as `completed++`, but `handleResult` returns `false`, breaking the loop. Clean shutdown.\n\n### Exit codes\n\nIf `LoopResult.failed > 0` after a phase command, `process.exit(1)`. Otherwise `process.exit(0)` (implicit). `doctor` also exits 1 if any check fails.\n\n### Stalled detection\n\nIf an agent session finishes without calling `task_complete`, the result is `{ status: \"stalled\" }`, which triggers the configured failure strategy.\n\n---\n\n## 9. Run Artifacts and Debugging\n\nPer-run artifacts written to `.super-ralph/runs/<runId>/`:\n\n```\nsession.json      — live state (status, counters, timestamps); also mirrored to .super-ralph/session.json\nevents.jsonl      — newline-delimited JSON event log ({ ts, event })\niterations/\n  001-<label>.log — per-iteration transcript (Display Stream + Raw Event Stream)\n```\n\nRun ID format: `<epochMs>-<random6chars>` (sorts chronologically).\n\nProgress log: `.super-ralph/progress.md` — Markdown append-only log with model, duration, cost, tokens, files changed, transcript path, and agent reason per iteration.\n\nDebug workflow:\n1. Check `.super-ralph/session.json` — is run still moving?\n2. Inspect `events.jsonl` — what was the last event and why?\n3. Open latest `iterations/*.log` — what did the agent actually do?\n\n---\n\n## 10. Templates and Customization\n\nThree Handlebars templates in `.super-ralph/` (copied from `templates/` during `init`, customizable per project):\n\n**`forward.hbs`** — receives: `epicId`, `beadId`, `beadTitle`, `beadDescription`, `beadLabels`, `beadDependsOn`, `readyCount`, `recentProgress`. Instructs agent on 11-step implementation workflow: read progress → inspect bead → implement → quality gates → self-review → commit → close bead → update progress → call `task_complete`.\n\n**`decompose.hbs`** — receives: `specContent`, `epicId`, `existingBeads[]`, `includeReview`, `includeBugscan`, `includeAudit`. Guides agent on bead sizing, dependency ordering, area labels, and when to signal `phase_done`.\n\n**`reverse.hbs`** — handles all three modes (interactive, autonomous, mixed) with `{{#if interactive}}` blocks. In interactive mode: enforces hard gate (no spec until interrogation complete), phases A (interrogation with `question` tool) and B (synthesis, incremental approval). In autonomous mode: first-iteration draft or iterative refinement with current spec content.\n\n---\n\n## 11. Skills System\n\nBuilt-in skills (question banks for the reverse phase):\n- `feature.md` — 12 questions: business interrogation + technical deep-dive\n- `bug.md` — investigation + technical questions\n- `hotfix.md` — minimal rapid-response questions\n- `refactor.md` — scope, risk, and approach questions\n\nSkills are selected with `--skill <name>` or `--skill <path/to/custom.md>`. Content is injected into the `reverse.hbs` template as `skillContent`. If no skill is provided, the template falls back to 7 universal baseline questions.\n\n---\n\n## 12. Testing Infrastructure\n\n**Unit tests** (`bun test`):\n- `tests/unit/run-artifacts.test.ts` — tests `startRunTracker` and `getRunStatus` (session creation, event recording, transcript writing, finalize, latest run resolution)\n- `tests/unit/reverse-mock-answers.test.ts` — tests that mock answers are cleared when `--answers` is not provided\n\n**E2E tests** (bash scripts):\n- `tests/e2e-all.sh` — suite runner; `--live` flag enables live tests\n- `tests/e2e-forward.sh`, `e2e-decompose.sh`, `e2e-reverse.sh`, `e2e-doctor.sh` — dry-run verification for each phase\n- `tests/e2e-live.sh`, `e2e-live-complex.sh` — live tests against real OpenCode server (requires API key)\n\n---\n\n## 13. Key Behavioral Contracts\n\n1. **Every agent session must call `task_complete`** — failure to do so results in `stalled` status and triggers failure strategy.\n2. **Each iteration gets a fresh session** — no context carries between iterations. The orchestrator passes state via the rendered prompt (recent progress, existing beads, current spec).\n3. **Phases communicate only via filesystem** — reverse writes specs, decompose reads specs and writes beads, forward reads beads. No in-process coupling.\n4. **Config is loaded once per run** — from `loadConfig(projectDir)` at the start of `runPhaseLoop`. Changes during a run are not picked up.\n5. **Server is always closed in `finally`** — even on exception or timeout, cleanup() runs.\n6. **`--dry-run` never starts a server** — iterates `nextIteration` to show what would run, returns immediately with zero counts.\n7. **`--attach` reuses an external server** — `close()` is a no-op; the external server is not shut down.\n8. **Transcript writing is best-effort** — if neither raw nor display output is captured, no `.log` file is written for that iteration.\n9. **Model resolution is deterministic** — CLI override > area label > default. Missing area label silently falls back to default.\n10. **Broken OpenCode symlinks are auto-fixed** — `startServer()` always runs `checkBrokenSymlinks({ fix: true })` before spawning.\n</task_result>",
